title: (x) Telenor corporate face - Telenor (proprietary) {Fabio}
content:
Can someone give an ID for this this type?   
 ![Telenor 01](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518124531im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/32733.gif)   
 ![Telenor 02](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518124531im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/32734.gif)
author: neuroman

comments.content:
This is a custom type by Magnus Rakeng!   
   
See here!   
 [http://www.melkeveien.no/magnus-rakeng/telenor.html](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518124531/http:/www.melkeveien.no/magnus-rakeng/telenor.html)

I visited the web sites and looked for more key letters, but it seems not to be one of the Sans Serif fonts I have in my [Guide](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518124531/http:/bowfinprintworks.com/SansIDPage.html). It resembles [T-26 Flux](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518124531/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/t26/flux/) and also their [Leger](http://web.archive.org/web/20050518124531/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/t26/leger/), but neither is exactly right. It also resembles DIN, but the stemless bowl on Telenor's 'b' does not match.   
   
It seems to be a Sans I have not catalogued, so I'm curious about it too.
Look what happened while I was off hunting! Thanks Fabio. I guess that explains why I haven't collected it yet.
